So are you team jiffy or team cornbread from scratch? 

I wasn’t raised on jiffy so I have always had a love for cornbread from scratch! It’s so simple anyone can make it! 

Ingredients*
2 cups cornmeal

2 cups flour

2 tablespoons of baking powder

1 1/2 cup sugar

2 1/2 cups buttermilk

1 cup vegetable oil 

5 eggs

3 tablespoons of butter

*Instructions:*

- Preheat oven to 350

- Take cornmeal, flour, sugar, and baking powder—put in a mixing bowl

-Whisk very well

- Make a well in the middle of the dry ingredients 

- Add in wet ingredients in the middle—buttermilk, oil, and eggs

- Stir until combined, but DO NOT overstir

- You will probably see some lumps in the mixture 

- Melt 3 tablespoons of butter

- Pour melted butter into baking dish & spread over the bottom of the dish.

- Pour cornbread mixture into baking dish. I use a 9 X 13 dish. 

- Bake on 350 degrees for 40-45 minutes, or until golden brown

- Once cornbread is done and out of the oven, immediately take BUTTER and rub it on top of the bread

Enjoy ☺️
